# borednomore3.list - Wallpaper pattern selection file
# Purpose: Specify which files to use as wallpapers using glob patterns
# Usage:
#   1. One pattern per line (wildcards allowed: * ? [ ] )
#   2. Lines starting with # are comments and ignored
#   3. Patterns are relative to the directory specified with -d/--directory
#   4. Run the changer with: python3 borednomore3.py -l borednomore3.list
#      (or -l custom.list if you renamed the file)
#   5. If the file is missing or empty → defaults to *.jpg *.png *.jpeg *.webp
#   6. You can use as many patterns as you want — all matches are combined

# === BASIC EXAMPLES ===
*.jpg                    # All JPEG files in the directory
*.png                    # All PNG files (great for images with transparency)
*.jpeg                   # Alternative JPEG extension (some cameras use it)
*.webp                   # Modern WebP format (smaller files, good quality)

# === MORE SPECIFIC WILDCARD EXAMPLES ===
# dark*.jpg                # All JPEG files starting with "dark" (dark_forest.jpg, dark_city.png, etc.)
# *_4k.*                   # Any file ending with _4k (any extension: image_4k.jpg, sunset_4k.png, etc.)
# wallpaper_*.jpg          # Files like wallpaper_00001.jpg, wallpaper_night.jpg, etc.
# cyberpunk_*.*            # All cyberpunk themed files (cyberpunk_city.jpg, cyberpunk_neon.png, etc.)

# === RANGE & CHARACTER CLASS EXAMPLES ===
# wallpaper_[0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9].jpg   # wallpaper_00000.jpg to wallpaper_99999.jpg
# photo_[ABC]*.png         # photo_A_something.png, photo_B_test.png, photo_C_123.png
# image_????.jpg           # image_ followed by exactly 4 characters (image_2023.jpg, image_abcd.jpg)

# === SUBFOLDER EXAMPLES ===
# nature/*.jpg             # All JPEGs inside a "nature" subfolder
# themes/cyberpunk/*.png   # All PNGs in themes/cyberpunk/
# minimal_landscapes/*.*   # Everything inside minimal_landscapes folder

# === MIXED & ADVANCED EXAMPLES ===
# *.jpg
# *.png
# dark*.*
# minimal_*.jpg
# 4k_*.*                   # All files starting with 4k_ (any extension)
# abstract_[0-9]*.png      # abstract_1.png, abstract_42.png, etc.
# */background_*.jpg       # All background_*.jpg files in ANY subfolder

# === TIPS ===
# - Use * for any characters (including none)
# - Use ? for exactly one character
# - Use [abc] for one character from the set a/b/c
# - Use [a-z] for any lowercase letter
# - Use [0-9] for any digit
# - Avoid very broad patterns like *.* (might include thumbnails, temp files, etc.)
